*Bug Variance*:
The same error might be thrown when re-running a build even soft-limit is not exceeded.

When an active job is stopped, a message will be logged:

{quote}
command	 28-Aug-2015 01:44:15 Request to stop 'XYZ' received from abc
{quote}

But "Status" on the build result summary page will be:

{quote}
Reason for not building is unknown.
{quote}

In this case, the status should be known.  Reporting "abc stopped build" would save time spent diagnosing failed builds when it turns out they were intentionally cancelled by other team members.

Similarly if a build is unsuccessful because of a Bamboo restart then it should be clear why the build failed to run.
